         <div>
            <head>7.6.1882 Mittwoch</head>
            <p>
               <placeName type="write" key="49097">Ascot</placeName> June 7.
      Wednesday 1882.</p>
            <p> We went round to look out for tramps this evening. We first went and
      burnt some magnesium wire before the different luminous paint pictures; after
      this we went on the heath and there watched some Gipsies undressing and going
      to bed. I heard one of the women say &#x201e;I was all a-shiverin&#x2019; and
      a&#x2019;shiverin&#x2019; with the cold today; and I was so uncomfortable
      &#x2019;cause I &#x2019;adn&#x2019;t washed today; but Lizzie was all right
      &#x2019;cause she &#x2019;ad&#x201c;. We burnt some Magnesium wire before them
      and they directly extinguished their fire. After this we went up the bog road
      and as we were throwing detonators someone hit an old man who was sitting on a
      fence; it did not go off nevertheless the old man got into a tremendous rage,
      and ran after us; thereupon there was a scramble to get over the garden gate
      which was locked. We all got over safely as the old man is supposed to have
      fallen; but I did not see him do so.</p>
